bizTalkServer.name: bizTalkServer

revisions.description: Refactored to match the Microsoft BizTalk 2006.
Changed the syntax of the datapoints from integer to gauge.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

bizTalkServer.description: The MIB module for SNMP Informant BizTalk performance counter entries.

bizTalkFILEReceiveAdapterTable.name: bizTalkFILEReceiveAdapterTable
bizTalkFILEReceiveAdapterTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'BizTalk:FILE Receive Adapter' objects.

bizTalkFILEReceiveAdapterEntry.name: bizTalkFILEReceiveAdapterEntry
bizTalkFILEReceiveAdapterEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'BizTalk:FILE Receive Adapter' object.

btfileraBytesReceived.name: btfileraBytesReceived
btfileraBytesReceived.description: Total number of bytes received by adapter. The counter is incremented after a message is completely read by the adapter from the file system.

btfileraBytesReceivedPerSec.name: btfileraBytesReceivedPerSec
btfileraBytesReceivedPerSec.description: Number of bytes received by adapter per second. The counter applies only to messages that have been completely read by the adapter from the file system.

btfileraDeleteRetries.name: btfileraDeleteRetries
btfileraDeleteRetries.description: Number of times adapter attempts to delete a file that has been read.

btfileraLockFailures.description: Number of times the file receive adapter failed to lock the file.

btfileraLockFailuresPerSec.name: btfileraLockFailuresPerSec
btfileraLockFailuresPerSec.description: Number of times file receive adapter failed to lock the file per second.

btfileraMessagesReceived.name: btfileraMessagesReceived
btfileraMessagesReceived.description: Total number of messages received by adapter. The counter is incremented after a message is completely read by the adapter from the file system.

btfileraMessagesReceivedPerSec.name: btfileraMessagesReceivedPerSec
btfileraMessagesReceivedPerSec.description: Number of messages received by adapter per second. The counter applies only to messages that have been completely read by the adapter from the file system.

btfileraTimeToBuildBatch.name: btfileraTimeToBuildBatch
btfileraTimeToBuildBatch.description: Average time taken by file receive adapter to build a batch

bthttpraTimeToAddMessageToBatch.description: Average time between when message is given to adapter by IIS and till message is added to a batch

bthttpraTimeToBuildBatch.name: bthttpraTimeToBuildBatch
bthttpraTimeToBuildBatch.description: Average time taken by adapter to build a batch

btmaActiveInstanceCount.name: btmaActiveInstanceCount
btmaActiveInstanceCount.description: The current number of active instances loaded in memory, including the standby instances

btmaDatabaseSession.name: btmaDatabaseSession
btmaDatabaseSession.description: Number of open database connections to the messagebox

btmaDatabaseSessionThreshold.name: btmaDatabaseSessionThreshold
btmaDatabaseSessionThreshold.description: The current threshold for the number of open database connections to the messagebox

btmaDatabaseSize.name: btmaDatabaseSize

btmaHighDatabaseSession.name: btmaHighDatabaseSession
btmaHighDatabaseSession.description: The number of currently opened database sessions exceeds the threshold

btmaHighDatabaseSize.name: btmaHighDatabaseSize
btmaHighDatabaseSize.description: The destination queue depth of all messagebox databases exceeds the threshold. If the host publishes to multiple queues, the weighted average across all destination queues is computed (based on recent publish statistics) and compared with the threshold

btmaHighInprocessMessageCount.name: btmaHighInprocessMessageCount
btmaHighInprocessMessageCount.description: The number of in-process messages exceeds the threshold

btmaHighMessageDeliveryRate.name: btmaHighMessageDeliveryRate
btmaHighMessageDeliveryRate.description: The message delivery rate is higher than the message processing rate

btmaHighMessagePublishingRate.name: btmaHighMessagePublishingRate
btmaHighMessagePublishingRate.description: The message publishing request rate is higher than the message publishing completion rate

btmaHighProcessMemory.name: btmaHighProcessMemory
btmaHighProcessMemory.description: The process memory consumption exceeds the threshold

btmaHighSystemMemory.name: btmaHighSystemMemory
btmaHighSystemMemory.description: The system-wide physical memory consumption exceeds the threshold

btmaHighThreadCount.name: btmaHighThreadCount
btmaHighThreadCount.description: The thread count exceeds the threshold

btmaInprocessMessageCount.name: btmaInprocessMessageCount
btmaInprocessMessageCount.description: The number of concurrent messages that the service class is processing

btmaInprocessMsgCountThreshold.name: btmaInprocessMsgCountThreshold
btmaInprocessMsgCountThreshold.description: The current threshold for the number of concurrent messages that the service class is processing

btmaMsgDeliveryDelayms.name: btmaMsgDeliveryDelayms
btmaMsgDeliveryDelayms.description: The delay injected in each batch for throttling the delivery of messages

btmaMsgDeliveryOutgoingRate.name: btmaMsgDeliveryOutgoingRate

btmaMsgDeliveryThrottlingState.name: btmaMsgDeliveryThrottlingState
btmaMsgDeliveryThrottlingState.description: The throttling state of the message delivery. A non-zero value indicates that the message delivery is being throttled due to one of the following reasons: 1- rate, 3- unprocessed message, 4- process memory, 5- system memory, 9- thread count, 10- user ove

btmaMsgDlvryThrottlingStDuration.name: btmaMsgDlvryThrottlingStDuration
btmaMsgDlvryThrottlingStDuration.description: Seconds spent in the current state (throttling or not throttling) of message delivery throttling

btmaMsgDlvryThrottleUserOverride.name: btmaMsgDlvryThrottleUserOverride
btmaMsgDlvryThrottleUserOverride.description: The user override for the message delivery

btmaMsgPublishingDelay.name: btmaMsgPublishingDelay
btmaMsgPublishingDelay.description: The delay injected in each qualifying batch for throttling the publishing of messages

btmaMsgPublishingIncomingRate.name: btmaMsgPublishingIncomingRate
btmaMsgPublishingIncomingRate.description: The number of message publish requests issued by the service class per second

btmaMsgPublishingOutgoingRate.name: btmaMsgPublishingOutgoingRate
btmaMsgPublishingOutgoingRate.description: The number of messages actually published by the service class per second

btmaMsgPublishingThrottlingState.name: btmaMsgPublishingThrottlingState
btmaMsgPublishingThrottlingState.description: The throttling state of the message publishing. A non-zero value indicates that the message publishing is being throttled due to one of the following reasons: 2- rate, 4- process memory, 5- system memory, 6- database size, 8- database session count, 9- th

btmaMsgPubThrottlingStDuration.name: btmaMsgPubThrottlingStDuration
btmaMsgPubThrottlingStDuration.description: Seconds spent in the current state (throttling or not throttling) of message publish throttling

btmaMsgPubThrottlingUsrOverride.name: btmaMsgPubThrottlingUsrOverride
btmaMsgPubThrottlingUsrOverride.description: The user override for the message publishing

btmaProcessMemoryUsageMB.name: btmaProcessMemoryUsageMB
btmaProcessMemoryUsageMB.description: The memory usage of current process (MB)

btmaProcessMemUsageThresholdMB.name: btmaProcessMemUsageThresholdMB
btmaProcessMemUsageThresholdMB.description: The current threshold for the memory usage of current process (MB). The threshold may be dynamically adjusted depending on the actual amount of memory available to this process and its memory consumption pattern

btmaServiceClassID.name: btmaServiceClassID
btmaServiceClassID.description: The decimal value of the initial part of the service class GUID that this performance counter instance corresponds to. A process may host more than one service class and the message agent performance counters show the data for the most active service clas

btmaThreadCount.name: btmaThreadCount
btmaThreadCount.description: The total number of threads in the process

btmaThreadCountThreshold.name: btmaThreadCountThreshold
btmaThreadCountThreshold.description: The current threshold for the total number of threads in the process

btmaTotalBatchesCommitted.name: btmaTotalBatchesCommitted
btmaTotalBatchesCommitted.description: Total number of batches committed by the service class

btmaTotalMessagesDelivered.name: btmaTotalMessagesDelivered
btmaTotalMessagesDelivered.description: The total number of messages delivered to the service class

btmaTotalMessagesPublished.name: btmaTotalMessagesPublished
btmaTotalMessagesPublished.description: The total number of messages published by the service class

btmbgcMsgBoxDeadProcCleanup.description: Time in seconds for most recent run of SQL agent job which releases database rows associated with dead BTS processes.

btmbgcMsgBoxMsgCleanupPurgeJobs.description: Time in seconds for most recent run of SQL agent job which cleans up message box tables associated with removed messages.

btmbgcMsgBoxPurgeSubPurgeJobs.description: Time in seconds for most recent run of SQL agent job which purges subscriptions which are no longer in use.

btmbgcSpoolSize.name: btmbgcSpoolSize
btmbgcSpoolSize.description: Spool size: Tracks the size of the spool on a particular message box on a particular server.

btmbgcTrackedMsgsCopyPurgeJobs.name: btmbgcTrackedMsgsCopyPurgeJobs
btmbgcTrackedMsgsCopyPurgeJobs.description: Time in seconds for most recent run of SQL agent job which copies tracked message bodies for tracked messages.

btmbgcTrackingDataSize.description: Tracking data size: Tracks the size of the tracking data table on a particular message box on a particular server.

btmbgcTrackingSpoolCleanup.name: btmbgcTrackingSpoolCleanup
btmbgcTrackingSpoolCleanup.description: Time in seconds for most recent run of SQL agent job which purges the inactive tracking spool tables.

bizTalkMessagingTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'BizTalk:Messaging' objects.

bizTalkMessagingEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'BizTalk:Messaging' object.

btmActiveReceiveLocations.name: btmActiveReceiveLocations

btmActiveReceiveThreads.name: btmActiveReceiveThreads
btmActiveReceiveThreads.description: Number of threads in the Messaging Engine currently processing messages received from adapters running in this host instance. These include messages that have been processed asynchronously by send adapters

btmActiveSendMessages.name: btmActiveSendMessages
btmActiveSendMessages.description: Number of messages the Messaging Engine has currently in send processing. This includes messages currently in send pipeline processing as well as response messages for receive adapters

btmActiveSendThreads.name: btmActiveSendThreads
btmActiveSendThreads.description: Number of threads in the Messaging Engine currently processing messages to send to adapters. This includes response messages to receive adapters

btmDocumentsResubmitted.name: btmDocumentsResubmitted
btmDocumentsResubmitted.description: Total number of documents resubmitted by send adapters

btmDocumentsSubmittedPerBatch.name: btmDocumentsSubmittedPerBatch
btmDocumentsSubmittedPerBatch.description: Average number of documents submitted per batch.

btmDocumentsTransmittedPerBatch.name: btmDocumentsTransmittedPerBatch
btmDocumentsTransmittedPerBatch.description: Average number of messages transmitted per batch.

btmIDProcess.name: btmIDProcess
btmIDProcess.description: The process identifier for this host instance

btmPendingReceiveBatches.name: btmPendingReceiveBatches
btmPendingReceiveBatches.description: Number of batches received by the Messaging Engine that have not completed processing. These include batches that have been processed asynchronously by send adapters

btmPendingTransmittedMessages.name: btmPendingTransmittedMessages
btmPendingTransmittedMessages.description: Number of messages given by the Messaging Engine to send adapters that have not completed processing. This includes response messages for receive adapters

btmRequestPerResponseTimeouts.name: btmRequestPerResponseTimeouts
btmRequestPerResponseTimeouts.description: Number of request messages that have not received a response message within the time limit specified by the adapter

btmThrottledReceiveBatches.name: btmThrottledReceiveBatches
btmThrottledReceiveBatches.description: Number of batches that have been blocked on receive by the Messaging Engine due to high service load. These batches contain new messages to be processed

btmlOutboundAdapterLatencysec.description: Average latency in seconds from when the adapter gets a document from the Messaging Engine until the time it is sent by the adapter.

btmlOutboundLatencysec.name: btmlOutboundLatencysec
btmlOutboundLatencysec.description: Average latency in seconds from when the Messaging Engine receives a document from the Message Box until the time document is sent by the adapter.

btmlRequestResponseLatencysec.name: btmlRequestResponseLatencysec
